    <!-- Main Content: Do's and What Not To Do -->
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Immediate Steps (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Clear the Area:</strong> Remove any dangerous objects and create a safe space.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ease the Person onto Their Side:</strong> Gently roll them onto their side to help keep the airway clear.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Time the Seizure:</strong> Note the duration for emergency responders.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Call Emergency Services:</strong> Dial your local emergency number if the seizure lasts longer than 5 minutes or if itâ€™s the first seizure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Stay Calm and Reassure:</strong> Remain with the person and offer calm reassurance until help arrives.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not restrain the person forcefully.</li>
          <li>Avoid putting any objects in their mouth.</li>
          <li>Do not move them unnecessarily.</li>
          <li>Do not panic or increase their distress.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-3">
          <em>Note:</em> This guide is for emergency use only and is not a substitute for professional medical advice.
        </p>
